UNITED STATES of America v. Charles WITT. No. 5134. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Jan. 18, 1934.

Before EVANS, SPARKS, and FITZ HENRY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of Edward A. Fisher, assistant United States attorney, counsel for appellant, it is now here ordered by this court that this» cause be docketed in this court instanter, and that this appeal bo, and the same is hereby, dismissed.
